 {"id":"bd-2hm","title":"Implement as_proxy() server composition","description":"# Server Composition: as_proxy()

## Background
Python FastMCP provides as_proxy() to create a proxy to an external MCP server. This enables composition with servers that run in separate processes or on remote hosts, creating a unified interface for clients.

## Requirements

### ServerBuilder API
```rust
impl ServerBuilder {
    /// Create a proxy to an external MCP server
    ///
    /// # Example
    /// ```rust
    /// // Proxy to a stdio server
    /// let main = Server::new("main", "1.0")
    ///     .as_proxy("external", StdioTransport::new("python", &["server.py"]))
    ///     .await?;
    ///
    /// // Proxy to an HTTP server
    /// let main = Server::new("main", "1.0")
    ///     .as_proxy("remote", HttpTransport::new("http://localhost:8080"))
    ///     .await?;
    /// ```
    pub async fn as_proxy<T: Transport>(
        self,
        prefix: &str,
        transport: T,
    ) -> Result<Self, ProxyError>
}
```

### Proxy Behavior
1. **Discovery**: Connect to external server, initialize, list tools/resources/prompts
2. **Registration**: Register proxy handlers for each discovered component
3. **Forwarding**: Proxy handlers forward calls to external server
4. **Lifecycle**: Maintain connection, handle reconnection on failure

### Proxy Handler Implementation
```rust
struct ProxyToolHandler {
    name: String,
    external_name: String,
    client: Arc<McpClient>,
    metadata: ToolMetadata, // Cached from discovery
}

impl ToolHandler for ProxyToolHandler {
    fn name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn description(&self) -> Option<&str> { self.metadata.description.as_deref() }
    fn tags(&self) -> &[String] { &self.metadata.tags }

    async fn call(&self, ctx: &McpContext, args: Value) -> McpResult<CallToolResult> {
        // Forward to external server
        self.client.call_tool(&self.external_name, args).await
    }
}
```

### Connection Management
- Lazy connection (connect on first use) vs eager (connect during as_proxy)
- Reconnection with exponential backoff
- Health checking / keep-alive
- Graceful shutdown

